---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About & Editorial Standards — AI Smart Tools"
  description="How we test, score, and rank AI productivity tools. Editorial standards and team at AI Smart Tools."
>
  <article class="container-prose py-12 md:py-16 prose-custom">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About AI Smart Tools</h1>
    
    <p class="lead">
      AI Smart Tools is an independent review site built by a small team of AI-tool obsessives who got tired of affiliate-stuffed listicles that were obviously written by someone who'd never opened the apps they were ranking.
    </p>
    
    <h2>What we believe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Real use beats real features.</strong> We test every tool before we rank it. A "spectacular AI feature" that crashes 3 times a week doesn't make our lists.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparency is non-negotiable.</strong> Every review page links to our affiliate disclosure at the top. Our scores are not for sale.</li>
      <li><strong>Updates matter.</strong> We re-test quarterly. If a tool drops, we say so. If a tool rises, we say so.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>How we test</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>We sign up using our own email and credit card (free trial first, then paid).</li>
      <li>We use the tool daily for at least 2 weeks before scoring.</li>
      <li>We rate on 4 axes: <strong>Ease of use</strong>, <strong>Quality of output</strong>, <strong>Integrations</strong>, <strong>Value</strong>.</li>
      <li>When two tools tie, the deciding factor is support responsiveness: we email support and time the response.</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      When you click an outbound link on AI Smart Tools and sign up for a paid plan, we may earn a commission.
      We never accept payment to boost a score. Read our full <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Email: <a href="mailto:hello@aismarttools.com">hello@aismarttools.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
